                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/6–149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-01">June 1,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received May 31—11:51 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1918. Reference my 1822, May 25. Believe all reports now in from American
                    organizations. There has been no loss of American life, some material damage to
                    properties. Shanghai University and China Bible Seminary in close proximity to
                    fighting emerged all safe.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
